led by human diversity","slug":"modern-racism-rests-on-scientific-theories-from-the-19th-century","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"Modern racism rests on scientific theories from the 19th century","standfirstLong":"Confused 17th-century Europeans argued that human groups were separately created, a precursor to racist thought today","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":true,"settings":{"badgeColor":null,"cardPlayIconColor":null,"alignX":"center","alignY":"center","backdropStrength":3},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"199129","name":"Jacob Zellmer"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/d5c0ee97-a6ad-480d-8307-3336dbf2090d/essay-nott_s_1857_ethnographic_tableau_specimens_of_various_races_of_mankind.jpg","alt":"Illustration of various human skulls and profiles with captions detailing different ethnic groups and regions, from a historical anthropological study.","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"History of ideas","slug":"history-of-ideas"},"topics":[{"slug":"history-of-ideas","title":"History of ideas"},{"slug":"race-and-ethnicity","title":"Race and ethnicity"},{"slug":"anthropology","title":"Anthropology"}],"section":{"title":"Philosophy","slug":"philosophy"},"createdAt":"2024-05-31T12:12:54Z"},{"id":"7316","title":"Philosophy was once alive","slug":"on-breaking-philosophy-out-of-the-seminar-and-back-into-the-world","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"On breaking philosophy out of the seminar and back into the world","standfirstLong":"I was searching for meaning and purpose so I became an academic philosopher. Reader, you might guess what happened next","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":true,"settings":{"badgeColor":null,"cardPlayIconColor":null,"alignX":"center","alignY":"top","backdropStrength":3},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"165995","name":"Pranay Sanklecha"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/8417518a-633e-40d4-8999-94842f5c5f17/essay-gettyimages-635967811.jpg","alt"